{
  "texts": [
    "These results confirm the shift toward integrated data-driven methodologies in modern financial research.",
    "Distribution by Financial DomainThe classification of the 22 studies into thematic areas is summarized in Table 2.",
    "Most papers belong to the stock market forecasting and asset pricing domain (8 studies), followed by credit risk and loan default prediction (6 studies), cryptocurrency and volatility forecasting (5 studies), and macroeconomic or policy forecasting (3 studies).",
    "Stock market and asset pricing studies show that ML can detect complex nonlinear dependencies and improve price forecasts beyond traditional models [34], [35].",
    "Credit risk research highlights the role of explainable AI tools such as SHAP in making ML outcomes more interpretable for banking supervision [36], [37]."
  ]
}